# [Rectangle Area](https://www.hackerrank.com/challenges/rectangle-area/problem?isFullScreen=true)
## Easy
<div class="challenge-body-html"><div class="challenge_problem_statement"><div class="msB challenge_problem_statement_body"><div class="hackdown-content"><svg style="display: none;"><defs id="MathJax_SVG_glyphs"></defs></svg><p>In this challenge, you are required to compute the area of a rectangle using classes. </p>

<p>Create two classes:</p>

<p><strong>Rectangle</strong>   </p>

<p>The <em>Rectangle</em> class should have two data fields-<em>width</em> and <em>height</em> of <em>int</em> types. The class should have <em>display()</em> method, to print the <em>width</em> and <em>height</em> of the rectangle separated by space.</p>

<p><strong>RectangleArea</strong></p>

<p>The <em>RectangleArea</em> class is derived from <em>Rectangle</em> class, i.e., it is the sub-class of <em>Rectangle</em> class. The class should have <em>read_input()</em> method, to read the values of <em>width</em> and <em>height</em> of the rectangle.
